Roebuck, and Company, having been always beloved by her coworkers for her attention to
detail and solicitude for her customers; during her work career and in her retirement, Mrs. Goins
also served as an Avon representative; and
WHEREAS, she was married to her beloved husband, Thomas Lace Goins, for sixty-four
years, a union blessed with three children, and she now enjoys a wealth of grandchildren and
great-grandchildren; and
WHEREAS, a woman of deep and abiding faith, Mrs. Goins is an eighty-year member of
Clinton Chapel AME Zion Church, where she is currently the oldest member of the
congregation; in addition to the daily bread of her religious television programming, she has
furthered her already intimate relationship with the Lord through generous service to Clinton
Chapel, including serving as Director of Christian Education, a Sunday School teacher, and
president of the Helen Spurgeon Circle Missionary Society; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Goins enjoyed playing bridge with the Saturday Night Cotillion Bridge
Club, and she was also a consistent community servant, whether through helping with early
voting or raising funds for service projects like the Heart Fund; her other interests include
watching her favorite game shows and listening to religious music and audio books; and
WHEREAS, a joy to be around and a blessing to all who have the good fortune of
knowing her, Mrs. Goins attributes her longevity to reading and studying the Bible, attending
Sunday School and church, and following the principles outlined in Matthew 7:12 and James
1:5-6; and
WHEREAS, as Mary Goins continues in her 104th year, she remains a beloved member
of her community who is admired for her wisdom, spirit of generosity, integrity, and enthusiasm
for life; and
WHEREAS, we wish to grasp this golden opportunity to specially recognize one of
Tennessee's most outstanding citizens on this very special occasion; now, therefore,
